HEADWORD: Parallel sulcus
<hw>Parallel sulcus</hw>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A sulcus parallel to,
but some distance below, the horizontal limb of the fissure of
Sylvius.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

